{"article_id":"7PP9CNwOKbLbkSA4","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"is a nonprofit newsroom","depth":3},{"id":1,"text":"that investigates abuses of power .","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"Sign up","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"to receive our biggest stories","depth":4},{"id":4,"text":"as soon as they ' re published .","depth":4},{"id":5,"text":"A nationwide shortage of two drugs","depth":11},{"id":6,"text":"touted as possible treatments for the coronavirus","depth":11},{"id":7,"text":"is being driven in part by doctors","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"inappropriately prescribing the medicines for family , friends and themselves ,","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"according to pharmacists and state regulators .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"\" It ' s disgraceful ,","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"is what it is , \"","depth":10},{"id":12,"text":"said Garth Reynolds , executive director of the Illinois Pharmacists Association ,","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"which started getting calls and emails Saturday from members","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"saying","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"they were receiving questionable prescriptions .","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"\" And completely selfish . \"","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"Demand for chloroquine and hydroxychloroquine surged over the past several days","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"as President Donald Trump promoted them as possible treatments for the coronavirus","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"and online forums buzzed with excitement over a small study","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"suggesting","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"the combination of hydroxychloroquine and a commonly used antibiotic could be effective","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"in treating COVID-19 .","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"Reynolds said","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"the Illinois Pharmacists Association has started reaching out to pharmacists and medical groups throughout the state","depth":11},{"id":25,"text":"to urge doctors , nurses and physician assistants not to write prescriptions for themselves and those close to them .","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"\" We even had a couple of examples of prescribers","depth":14},{"id":27,"text":"trying to say","depth":15},{"id":28,"text":"that the individual","depth":17},{"id":29,"text":"they were calling in for","depth":17},{"id":30,"text":"had rheumatoid arthritis , \"","depth":16},{"id":31,"text":"he said ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"explaining","depth":13},{"id":33,"text":"that pharmacists suspected","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"that wasn ' t true .","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"\" I mean ,","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"that ' s fraud . \"","depth":12},{"id":37,"text":"In one case ,","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"Reynolds said ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"the prescriber initially tried to get the pills","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"without an explanation","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"and only offered up","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"that the individual had rheumatoid arthritis","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"after the pharmacist questioned the prescription .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"In a bulletin to pharmacists on Sunday , the state association wrote","depth":9},{"id":45,"text":"that it was \" disturbed by the current actions of prescribers \"","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"and instructed members on how to file a complaint against physicians and nurses","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"who were doing it .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"\" People are losing their minds about this product , \"","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"said Brian Brito , president of SMP Pharmacy Solutions in Miami .","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"\" We ' re selling so much of this stuff","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"and people are just stockpiling it prophylactically","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"if anybody in their family gets sick -","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"they ' re just holding on to it . \"","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"Get Our Top Investigations","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"Subscribe to the Big Story newsletter .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"The two drugs are only available through a prescription","depth":7},{"id":57,"text":"and can not be purchased over the counter .","depth":7},{"id":58,"text":"Hydroxychloroquine ,","depth":9},{"id":59,"text":"sold under the brand name Plaquenil ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"is approved","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"to treat lupus and rheumatoid arthritis","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"while chloroquine is an anti-malarial treatment .","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"There is little evidence","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"that the drugs work","depth":10},{"id":65,"text":"to treat coronavirus ,","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"although clinical trials are underway","depth":9},{"id":67,"text":"to find out .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":69,"text":"as coronavirus cases multiply","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"and protective gear for medical workers vanishes from emergency rooms ,","depth":10},{"id":71,"text":"many patients and physicians see the drugs as the only hope","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"to reverse the course of serious disease .","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"Brito said","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"his pharmacy had about 800 tablets on Monday","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"and were nearly sold out in about an hour .","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"One doctor called","depth":12},{"id":77,"text":"and asked for 200 tablets ,","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"but the company refused .","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"\" He was a little upset about it","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"but he understood","depth":13},{"id":81,"text":"and he went quickly from 200 to 42 tablets ,","depth":14},{"id":82,"text":"which is essentially treating two people , \"","depth":14},{"id":83,"text":"Brito said .","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"\" So yeah , they ' re stockpiling it . \"","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"A pharmacist in Houston ,","depth":11},{"id":86,"text":"who asked to remain anonymous for fear of retaliation and violating patient privacy ,","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"said","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"he was recently asked by a surgeon for an unusually large quantity with unlimited refills .","depth":9},{"id":89,"text":"\" He said","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"it was because his wife had lupus , \"","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"the pharmacist said ,","depth":10},{"id":92,"text":"\" but","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"when I asked him for her name and diagnosis ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"he told me just to put it in his . \"","depth":11},{"id":95,"text":"Lupus patients are reporting difficulty","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"in refilling their prescriptions for the drug .","depth":5},{"id":97,"text":"On Monday , the Lupus Foundation of America issued a joint statement","depth":9},{"id":98,"text":"asking the White House Coronavirus Task Force to \" take action","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"to ensure","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"current supplies are allocated for patients","depth":12},{"id":101,"text":"taking them for indicated uses. \"","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"Several states in the past few days have already moved to limit prescriptions of the drugs ,","depth":9},{"id":103,"text":"neither of which is approved","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"to treat the coronavirus .","depth":10},{"id":105,"text":"Trump , in press conferences and tweets over the past week , has promoted the use of the drugs as potentially blunting the impact of the COVID-19 outbreak .","depth":7},{"id":106,"text":"Read More","depth":6},{"id":107,"text":"Lupus Patients Can ' t Get Crucial Medication","depth":7},{"id":108,"text":"After President Trump Pushes Unproven Coronavirus Treatment","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"Trump ' s unproven claim","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"that hydroxychloroquine could be used","depth":14},{"id":111,"text":"to treat COVID-19","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"has led to hoarding ,","depth":12},{"id":113,"text":"putting Lupus patients and others at even greater risk .","depth":11},{"id":114,"text":"As of Saturday afternoon , Anna Valdez had 27 pills left .","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"That number is now down to 25 .","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"\" It ' s unfortunate that a news conference ,","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"I think prematurely ,","depth":14},{"id":118,"text":"made it sound like this was the answer ,","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"and that ' s led to this panic , \"","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"Michelle Petri , director of Johns Hopkins University School of Medicine ' s Lupus Center , said Friday .","depth":11},{"id":121,"text":"\" I have spent the last two days","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"trying to help lupus patients","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"who actually need their refills. \"","depth":13},{"id":124,"text":"She said","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"some patients have refills on back order","depth":13},{"id":126,"text":"while others are being provided smaller amounts than usual .","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"The West Virginia Board of Pharmacy , in an alert Saturday , ordered pharmacists to limit new prescriptions to no more than 30 tablets and only to cases","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"where the drugs were being used for approved indications .","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"\" Currently , both nationally and in West Virginia , some prescribers have begun writing prescriptions for these drugs for family , friends , and coworkers in anticipation of Covid-19 related illness , \"","depth":11},{"id":130,"text":"the board wrote .","depth":11},{"id":131,"text":"Texas and Ohio have also restricted prescribing of the drugs .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"Louisiana on Sunday also issued an emergency rule","depth":13},{"id":133,"text":"limiting when the drugs can be prescribed ,","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"citing \" inappropriate use \" and \" hoarding. \"","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"On Monday , the Louisiana Board of Pharmacy said","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"it was rescinding that order","depth":13},{"id":137,"text":"because manufacturers had boosted distribution of the drugs .","depth":13},{"id":138,"text":"Experts are warning","depth":10},{"id":139,"text":"that any use of the drugs outside of a hospital setting can be dangerous ,","depth":10},{"id":140,"text":"and admonished doctors to stop prescribing the medicines inappropriately .","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"Daniel Brooks , the medical director of the Banner Poison and Drug Information Center in Phoenix , said","depth":13},{"id":142,"text":"it was \" immoral \" for physicians to hoard the medications .","depth":13},{"id":143,"text":"\" One should not be selfish and scared , especially medical providers , \"","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"he said .","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"\" I find it incredibly embarrassing and unfortunate","depth":12},{"id":146,"text":"that physicians appear to be prescribing these medications inappropriately . \"","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"This weekend Brooks cared for a man in his 60s","depth":13},{"id":148,"text":"who died","depth":13},{"id":149,"text":"after ingesting a version of chloroquine","depth":13},{"id":150,"text":"commonly used","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"to clean fish tanks .","depth":14},{"id":152,"text":"The man ,","depth":14},{"id":153,"text":"who thought","depth":15},{"id":154,"text":"he might have COVID-19 ,","depth":15},{"id":155,"text":"took a small amount of the substance in a misguided effort","depth":14},{"id":156,"text":"to treat his symptoms .","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"His wife was also hospitalized","depth":15},{"id":158,"text":"after taking the substance","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"but survived .","depth":14},{"id":160,"text":"Brooks said","depth":14},{"id":161,"text":"the amount","depth":16},{"id":162,"text":"the couple ingested","depth":16},{"id":163,"text":"was equivalent to a couple days ' worth of prescription chloroquine .","depth":15},{"id":164,"text":"Ken Thai , the owner of a chain of Los Angeles-area pharmacies , said","depth":13},{"id":165,"text":"his stores are witnessing a rash of inappropriate prescribing .","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"\" A lot of physicians , unfortunately , are writing high amounts for more than the required number of tablets","depth":15},{"id":167,"text":"and calling in five , six , seven and eight prescriptions at a time , \"","depth":15},{"id":168,"text":"he said .","depth":14},{"id":169,"text":"\" I don ' t want to insinuate what is going on ,","depth":14},{"id":170,"text":"but it is very unusual . \"","depth":14},{"id":171,"text":"He said","depth":13},{"id":172,"text":"his pharmacists are declining to fill suspicious orders","depth":14},{"id":173,"text":"and telling prescribers","depth":15},{"id":174,"text":"they don ' t have enough of the medication on hand","depth":16},{"id":175,"text":"to complete those requests .","depth":16},{"id":176,"text":"Among the prescriptions","depth":15},{"id":177,"text":"flagged are those for people","depth":16},{"id":178,"text":"who have not previously taken the drug","depth":16},{"id":179,"text":"as well as orders from doctors","depth":15},{"id":180,"text":"who do not typically treat lupus and rheumatoid arthritis patients .","depth":15},{"id":181,"text":"\" If a doctor is writing a prescription for himself or aunts and uncles ,","depth":16},{"id":182,"text":"that is usually a red flag for us , \"","depth":16},{"id":183,"text":"he said .","depth":15},{"id":184,"text":"\" Whatever we have in stock ,","depth":15},{"id":185,"text":"we have to preserve for the patients","depth":16},{"id":186,"text":"we currently service . \"","depth":16},{"id":187,"text":"On Twitter , pharmacy workers traded stories about dentists and opthamologists","depth":13},{"id":188,"text":"requesting hydroxychloroquine under dubious pretenses .","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"\" A dentist just tried to call in scripts for hydroxychloroquine + azithromycin for himself , his wife , & another couple","depth":15},{"id":190,"text":"( friends ) , \"","depth":15},{"id":191,"text":"tweeted a pharmacist in Eugene , Oregon .","depth":14},{"id":192,"text":"\" I have patients with lupus","depth":14},{"id":193,"text":"that have been on HCQ","depth":17},{"id":194,"text":"[ Hydroxychloroquine ]","depth":17},{"id":195,"text":"for YEARS","depth":16},{"id":196,"text":"and now can ' t get it","depth":16},{"id":197,"text":"because it ' s on backorder . \"","depth":16},{"id":198,"text":"Steve Moore , president of the Pharmacists Society of the State of New York , said","depth":13},{"id":199,"text":"medical providers","depth":15},{"id":200,"text":"hoarding the drugs","depth":15},{"id":201,"text":"is occuring in the state ,","depth":15},{"id":202,"text":"which has the highest number of coronavirus cases in the country .","depth":15},{"id":203,"text":"\" That ' s a double whammy , \"","depth":14},{"id":204,"text":"he said .","depth":14},{"id":205,"text":"\" We ' re potentially taking that medication away from patients with autoimmune conditions and patients with the actual virus","depth":14},{"id":206,"text":"that may need treatment . \"","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"Tell Us More About Coronavirus","depth":3},{"id":208,"text":"Are you a public health worker , medical provider , elected official , patient or other COVID-19 expert ?","depth":5},{"id":209,"text":"Help make sure","depth":7},{"id":210,"text":"our journalism is responsible","depth":8},{"id":211,"text":"and focused on the right issues .","depth":8},{"id":212,"text":"This form requires JavaScript","depth":7},{"id":213,"text":"to complete .","depth":7},{"id":214,"text":"Powered by Screendoor .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":429,"left":219,"right":428,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":219,"left":216,"right":218,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":216,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":218,"left":2,"right":217,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":217,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":428,"left":420,"right":427,"rel